X
M(X)
X
\mathbb{P}(X>M(X)),\mathbb{P}(X<M(X))\leq 1/2
M(X)=\mathbb{E}(X)+O((\mathbb{Var}(X))^{1/2})
\sigma=(\mathbb{Var}(X))^{1/2}
\mathbb{P}(X>\lambda \sigma)\leq \mathbb{P}(|X|>\lambda \sigma)\leq \frac{1}{\lambda ^2}
 \left|M(X)-\mathbb{E}(X)\right|=\left|\mathbb{E}(M(X)-X)\right| \\ \leq \mathbb{E}(\left|X-M(X)\right|)\leq \mathbb{E}(\left|X-\mathbb E(X)\right|) \\ \leq \sqrt{\mathbb{E}(\left|X-\mathbb E(X)\right|^2)}=(\mathbb{Var}(X))^{1/2}. 
